title: Updating the IStateOptions.reload to allow string or IState
body:
Improvement to existing type definition.

`reload` allows for a string based state or a state object (http://angular-ui.github.io/ui-router/site/#/api/ui.router.state.$state)

```
reload (v0.2.5) - {boolean=false|string|object}, If true will force transition even if no state or params have changed. It will reload the resolves and views of the current state and parent states. If reload is a string (or state object), the state object is fetched (by name, or object reference); and \ the transition reloads the resolves and views for that matched state, and all its children states.
```

title: ssh2: some options were not optional in ConnectConfig
body:
Case 2. Improvement to existing type definition.

It was not possible to create `ssh2.ConnectConfig` without specifying `tryKeyboard` and `debug` options which should be optional.

> tryKeyboard - boolean - Try keyboard-interactive user authentication if primary user authentication method fails. If you set this to true, you need to handle the keyboard-interactive event. Default: false
> 
> debug - function - Set this to a function that receives a single string argument to get detailed (local) debug information. Default: (none)

Source: https://github.com/mscdex/ssh2/blob/master/README.md#client-methods

title: Dojo xhr
body:
See #9338 

The current definitions for the dojo/request/xhr module don't match the source code; the helper methods (get, post, etc) are exposed in the definitions file, but commented out in the code.

In addition, the base xhr method returns either a promise or a deferred, but the definitions have it returning void, which makes using then, etc. impossible.  The default return type is a Promise, which is what I have set it to in the definitions.

See: https://github.com/dojo/dojo/blob/1.10/request/xhr.js

title: corrected case on showdownjs where "Converter" had been assigned the
body:
case 1. Add a new type definition.
- [X] checked compilation succeeds with `--target es6` and `--noImplicitAny` options.
- [X] has correct [naming convention](http://definitelytyped.org/guides/contributing.html#naming-the-file)

case 2. Improvement to existing type definition.
- documentation or source code reference which provides context for the suggested changes.  url https://github.com/showdownjs/showdown .
  - it has been reviewed by a DefinitelyTyped member.

The typings for `showdownjs` had an incorrect typing; the function `Converter()` was at some point changed to have uppercasing instead of being lowercase, `converter`. This was causing an issue where attempts to run code that was typed correctly would throw errors, and attempts to write code that runs correctly would throw errors with the typescript definitions.

The appropriate syntax for the `Converter` function is seen here, taken from the [project's documentation](https://github.com/showdownjs/showdown)

```
var converter = new showdown.Converter(),
    text      = '#hello, markdown!',
    html      = converter.makeHtml(text);
```

This update has resolved the identifier.

title: redux-actions: Un-restrict types of payload and reducer state
body:
Issued here #9376 

Currently the types of reducer state and action payload are restricted to be equal.

```
 type Reducer<Payload> = (state: Payload, action: Action<Payload>) => Payload;
```

This isn't right because reducer state has nothing to do with the payload.
This pull request added a new type parameter `State` for all type definitions with this restriction.

title: Inferrable _.assign*, _.extend*, _.defaults
body:
Following the pattern that 4e4ffc7e used for `_.merge`, redefine `_.assign*`, `_.extend*` and `_.defaults` to use intersection types. This means that almost all normal usages are able to infer much more informative types than just `{}`.

A few random notes about these changes: 
- Split tests for `_.extend` into a suite just for `_.extendWith`.
- I wasn't able to find a clever method for aliasing `extend` as `assignIn` without just copy-pasting it it (I tried playing around with `typeof`, etc).
- `_.defaults`'s return types' ordering is backwards from that in the parameter list because it appears that Typescript uses "latest wins" to resolve an intersection of types that define the same field name. Doing it backwards ensures that earlier parameters, which are later in the type expression, take precedence.
- Uncommented the `lodash/extendWith` module export since it exists now.

title: TypeScript-STL v0.9.7
body:
# TypeScript-STL v0.9.7 (2016-05-20)
##### Finally, TypeScript-STL v1.0 is approaching.

Most of Standard Template Libraries are implemented. Throughing tests and feedbacks for few months, TypeScript-STL will be published as v1.0.
##### Refatored for preparing Collection.

The future's **Collection** library, observes elements I/O. You can detect inserted and deleted elements by using `callback function` or `addEventListener` function. Those **Collection** containers will be implemented by inheriting containers in this **TypeScript-STL**.

The **Collection containers** may be named such like:
- ICollection -> implements std.base.IContainer, samchon.library.IEventDispatcher
- Linear Collections
  - ArrayCollection -> extends std.Vector
  - ListCollection -> extends std.List
  - DequeCollection -> extends std.Deque
- Hash & Tree Collections
  - HashSetCollection -> extends std.HashSet
  - HashMapCollection -> extends std.HashMap
  - TreeSetCollection -> extends std.TreeSet
  - TreeMapCollection -> extends std.TreeMap
- XMLListCollection
  - extends samchon.library.XMLList 
  - implements ICollection

The **Container** library will be realized in **Samchon Framework**.
- `namespace samchon.collection`
- Samchon Framework: https://github.com/samchon/framework
##### Fix errors on sequence specified ordering in tree containers.
- Wrong sequence ordering doesn't be occured.
- Inserting an element with hint works correctly.
#### Reverse iterators are separated from formal iterators.

Derived (non-basic) iterators do not inherit formal iterators. It will enhance type checking and prevent mistakes using reverse and formal iterators, in some functions getting range iterators, at the same time.
###### Reverse iterator do not extends formal iterator

``` java
// ORDINARY REVERSE_ITERATOR
class VectorReverseIterator<T> 
    extends VectorIterator<T> 
    implements base.IReverseIterator<T>;

// NEWELY UPDATED REVERSE_ITERATOR
class VectorReverseIterator<T>
    extends ReverseIterator<VectorIterator<T>>
```
###### Enhanced Type Checks

``` java
let vector: std.Vector<number> = new std.Vector<number(5, 1);
vector.erase(vector.begin(), vector.rend()); 
    // Invalid range iterators, formal and reverse iterators are used at the same time
    // IT CAUSES COMPILE ERROR FROM NOW ON
```
##### API Documents are enhanced.

Comments for API documents generation on basic objects are on fill.
- http://samchon.github.io/stl/api
##### Class Diagram is re-designed.

Class Diagram represents the **TypeScript-STL** is re-designed and published.
- http://samchon.github.io/stl/design/class_diagram.pdf
